    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two-dimensional geographical emissions data with categorical regions (nominal scale) and quantitative CO\u2082 values (ratio scale). Synthetic data maintains real-world magnitude relationships (\u03bc=1450, \u03c3=2480 for Asia; \u03bc=320, \u03c3=220 for Europe) while preserving actual country rankings. The packed bubble chart effectively encodes three variables: region (color), country (label), and emissions (bubble size + color intensity). This design follows Tufte's principles by maximizing data-ink through direct size-color mapping and Cairo's perceptual topology through proportional area encoding. The color progression (blue \u2192 red) leverages luminance contrast for pre-attentive regional discrimination. Quantitative anchors maintain interpretability: bubble sizes scale logarithmically to accommodate the 3-order magnitude range (6.5-10,540.8M tons)."
